senses.sense_text:
witness, testimony; martyr (one who witnessed unto death) 
(1) a judicial witness, deponent, testimony Mt. 18:16; Heb. 10:28; 
(2) generally, a witness to a circumstance, Lk. 24:48; Acts 10:41; in NT a witness, a testifier, of a doctrine, Rev. 1:5; 3:14; 11:3; 
(3) a martyr, Acts 22:20; Rev. 2:13
